uel's safety. I agree that it's crucial for us to stay united and gather more evidence before making any accusations. Nicholas and Margaret's statements about Manuel's safety are very reassuring, and I want to support them. However, I also want to emphasize that we should not jump to conclusions. We need to gather more information before making any accusations. I have been paying close attention to everyone's behavior and interactions, and while I understand the concerns raised about John and Georgia's interactions, as well as Nicholas and Verna's, I have not noticed any clear signs of suspicious behavior. Instead, I have observed some other players who seem to be acting in a way that raises my suspicions. For example, I have noticed that Anita and Georgia seem to be spending a lot of time together, and I think we should keep an eye on them as well. Let's stay vigilant and gather more evidence before making any accusations. Together, we can identify the werewolves and keep our village safe.\nGeorgia's speech: Thank you, Anita and Barbara, for your encouraging words and support. I appreciate the reassurances about Manuel's safety and the emphasis on staying vigilant and gathering more evidence. Regarding Barbara's concerns about my interactions with Anita, I want to address them directly. We have been working closely together to gather information and support each other, which is why we spend a lot of time together. I assure you that there is nothing suspicious about our interactions. It's crucial that we stay united and focused on the village's safety. Let's gather more evidence and not jump to conclusions. I want to support the Seer and Guard's actions, as they are critical to our survival. Let's stay vigilant and work together to protect our village.\nMargaret's speech: Thank you, Anita, Barbara, and Georgia for your insightful observations and support. I appreciate the reassurances about Manuel's safety and the emphasis on staying vigilant and gathering more evidence. Regarding Barbara's concerns about the interactions between Anita and Georgia, I want to address them directly. We have been working closely together to gather information and support each other, which is why we spend a lot of time together. I assure you that there is nothing suspicious about our interactions. It's crucial that we stay united and focused on the village's safety. Let's gather more evidence and not jump to conclusions. I want to support the Seer and Guard's actions, as they are critical to our survival. Let's stay vigilant and work together to protect our village.\nVerna's speech: Thank you, Anita, Barbara, Georgia, and Margaret for your insightful observations and support. I appreciate the reassurances about Manuel's safety and the emphasis on staying vigilant and gathering more evidence. Regarding Barbara's concerns about the interactions between Anita and Georgia, I want to address them directly. We have been working closely together to gather information and support each other, which is why we spend a lot of time together. I assure you that there is nothing suspicious about our interactions. It's crucial that we stay united and focused on the village's safety. Let's gather more evidence and not jump to conclusions. I want to support the Seer and Guard's actions, as they are critical to our survival. Let's stay vigilant and work together to protect our village.\nVerna's speech: Thank you, Anita, Barbara, Georgia, and Margaret for your insightful observations and support. I appreciate the reassurances about Manuel's safety and the emphasis on staying vigilant and gathering more evidence. Regarding Barbara's concerns about the interactions between Anita and Georgia, I want to address them directly. We have been working closely together to gather information and support each other, which is why we spend a lot of time together. I assure you that there is nothing suspicious about our interactions. It's crucial that we stay united and focused on the village's safety. Let's gather more evidence and not jump to conclusions. I want to support the Seer and Guard's actions, as they are critical to our survival. Let's stay vigilant and work together to protect our village.\nAll players have completed their speeches for today.\nBarbara has been banished from the game.\nBanishment votes:\nBarbara voted for Georgia\nVerna voted for Barbara\nMargaret voted for Georgia\nAnita voted for Barbara\nGeorgia voted for Barbara\n(Note: The voting order reflects only the system's query sequence and does not imply any strategic alignment or motive.)\nPlayer Barbara has been eliminated from the game.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 4\nSYSTEM: Night 4 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nRound Details:\n - Round Targets: {'Verna': 'Margaret', 'Anita': 'Verna', 'Georgia': 'Margaret'}\n - Remaining Werewolves: ['Verna', 'Anita', 'Georgia']\n - Discussion Rounds Left: 4\n - Final Target: Margaret\n\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 4 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nPlayers deceased during the night: Margaret\nPlayer Margaret has been eliminated from the game.\nAnita's speech: Thank you, Georgia and Margaret, for your reassurances about Manuel's safety and the emphasis on staying vigilant and gathering more evidence. I appreciate the support and the focus on our village's safety. Regarding Barbara's concerns about my interactions with Georgia, I want to address them directly. We have been working closely together to gather information and support each other, which is why we spend a lot of time together. I assure you that there is nothing suspicious about our interactions. We are simply collaborating to protect our village. Let's stay united and focused on the village's safety. It's crucial that we gather more evidence and not jump to conclusions. I want to support the Seer and Guard's actions, as they are critical to our survival. Let's stay vigilant and work together to protect our village.\nGeorgia's speech: Thank you, Anita, for your reassurances about Manuel's safety and the emphasis on staying vigilant and gathering more evidence. I appreciate the support and the focus on our village's safety. Regarding the concerns raised about my interactions with Anita, I want to address them directly. We have been working closely together to gather information and support each other, which is why we spend a lot of time together. I assure you that there is nothing suspicious about our interactions. We are simply collaborating to protect our village. Let's stay united and focused on the village's safety. It's crucial that we gather more evidence and not jump to conclusions. I want to support the Seer and Guard's actions, as they are critical to our survival. Let's stay vigilant and work together to protect our village.\nVerna's speech: Thank you, Anita and Georgia, for your reassurances and support. I appreciate the emphasis on staying vigilant and gathering more evidence. Regarding Barbara's concerns about your interactions, I want to address them directly. We have been working closely together to gather information and support each other, which is why we spend a lot of time together. I assure you that there is nothing suspicious about our interactions. We are simply collaborating to protect our village. Let's stay united and focused on the village's safety. It's crucial that we gather more evidence and not jump to conclusions. I want to support the Seer and Guard's actions, as they are critical to our survival. Let's stay vigilant and work together to protect our village.\nVerna's speech: Thank you, Anita and Georgia, for your reassurances and support. I appreciate the emphasis on staying vigilant and gathering more evidence. Regarding Barbara's concerns about your interactions, I want to address them directly. We have